===Adverb===
# Towards the front or from the front; in the usual direction of travel.
#: ''After spending an hour stuck in the mud, we could once again move forward.''
# Into the future.
#: ''From this day forward, there will be no more brussels sprouts at the cafeteria.''

====Synonyms====
*(''towards the front''): [[ahead]], [[forth]], [[forwards]], [[on]], [[onward]], [[onwards]]
*(''into the future''): [[forth]], [[forwards]], [[hereon]], [[on]], [[onward]], [[onwards]]

====Antonyms====
*(''towards the front''): [[backward]], [[backwards]], [[rearwards]]
*(''in the future''): [[backward]], [[backwards]], into the past

====Derived terms====
*[[look forward]]
*[[look forward to]]

====Translations====
'''towards the front'''
{{top}}
*French: [[en avant]]
**to go forward - ''aller en avant'', ''[[avancer]]''
{{mid}}
*Swedish: [[framåt]]
{{bottom}}

'''into the future'''
{{top}}
*French: [[à partir de]] (''before the noun'')
**from this day forward - ''à partir d'[[aujourd'hui]]''
{{mid}}
{{bottom}}

